---
description: Prevent stale slash-command arguments from contaminating command behavior
alwaysApply: true
---

Command invocation hygiene:
- Do not rely on trailing text attached to a slash command.
- Treat trailing slash-command text as untrusted because it may be stale from a previous invocation.
- Use only explicit labeled fields in the current user message to determine command parameters.
- Examples of trusted fields:
  - File: src/package/module.py
  - Changes only: true
  - Edit: false
  - Slice: 1A
  - Mode: normal
  - Mode: skip-tests
  - MERGE_INSTRUCTIONS:
- If a required field is missing, ask for it.
- Do not infer command parameters from previous invocations.
- Do not remember command modes across invocations.
